# for release
credentials

# Firebase config — gitignored because it is per-environment (prod vs dev/staging)
# and not a "secret" per se but should not be committed. Provisioning:
# - Local dev: download from the Firebase Console (LLC project for prod, or your
#   own throwaway project for end-to-end testing) and drop at the path below.
# - CI: a stub file is generated by ci.yml so the google-services plugin gets
#   exercised — no real config is needed for unit tests.
# - Release workflows (future): inject the real config from a private secret.
# Absent file → google-services plugin is skipped, FCM lib is bundled but inert.
apps/clientApp/google-services.json

